org.pircbotx.hooks.managers

Class ThreadedListenerManager<E extends PircBotX>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pircbotx.hooks.managers.ThreadedListenerManager<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ListenerManager<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BackgroundListenerManager

    public class ThreadedListenerManager<E extends PircBotX>
extends Object
implements ListenerManager<E>
    Wraps a ListenerManager and adds multithreading to dispatchEvent(org.pircbotx.hooks.Event). This makes dispatchEvent(org.pircbotx.hooks.Event) return almost immediately freeing up the bot to execute other incoming events

    This multithreading can be controlled with the perHook flag in the constructors.

    • false - Default. Listeners are executed sequentially in a separate thread per event.
    • true - Every listener is executed in a different thread all at once per event.
    Author:
    Leon Blakey
